ascents.name: Beefcake
ascents.comment: Could be 3 stars if it wasn't for the dab factor. Super cool line though. Shout out Nico and Scott for pad caddying for my send.

ascents.name: *Acid Wash
ascents.comment: The only thing we have to fear is fear itself. Well that and "One of Anything" bets. And now my dear Shirley, you shall know the meaning of fear, fear of never knowing when I'll get your ass. Oh and as for the climb, I'm happy to be done with this section of the boulder.

ascents.name: Invincible
ascents.comment: First of the grade! What an awesome climb. Shout out to people leaving stash pads, Squamish for having unseasonably dry weather, and coffee/gummy worms for getting me up this. Definitely an area I'll be happy to come back to for Cruelty and Splendor at some point...

ascents.name: Hormonal Monkey
ascents.comment: Meh. Just pinch hard.

ascents.name: Mindbender Low
ascents.comment: Whew. Finally. While waiting for friends climbing Golden Boy, I worked these moves and finally got it today in the worst conditions yet with my body the most sore it's been all trip. Surprisingly fun for being low to the ground.

ascents.name: The Words of Me
ascents.comment: Super soft. Probably 4 goes. But I did have some quality beta from the Spanish power couple of David and Judy! Made it look awful though when I stood up on my shoelace and almost fell on my send go because of the dumb long laces on my Oracle's...

ascents.name: Tatonka
ascents.comment: Well the guidebook says V9... and I really want a cool first V9... so I'll take it! But wow is it soft. Freaking amazing movement and a mix of three different betas from people of three different nationalities all sending together was something really cool and special. Wish I had some sandbox boys with me to celebrate tonight...

ascents.name: Mr. Bigglesworth
ascents.comment: Would be 3 starts if it had a better landing, but still fun! Wish I had flashed, but I tried this like 5 years ago so I guess just an M Flash.

ascents.name: Missing in action
ascents.comment: Very cool night send with Katie following me right up! Awesome to run into strong climbers from socal on their own road trip to Alaska and spend a couple days climbing with them!

ascents.name: Missing Reaction
ascents.comment: A much easier variation, but still fun movement! Might have enjoyed it more than missing in action, but a hell of a last day climbing on Squamish!

ascents.name: Busted
ascents.comment: One last moderate to finish my trip before heading to Squamish. Skin was thin, psych was high.

ascents.name: Pretty Hate Machine
ascents.comment: This is cool. And my beta is... Cooler. Swinging feet, high heels, delicate throws and should have sent in a sesh. But I came back for more after babying out of the last move about 5 too many times and put it down so it's definitely still soft. But definitely LeavenWORTH your while.

ascents.name: The Lion's Den
ascents.comment: Such a cool area. And really good conversation partners, Cassidy and Paul, had lots of book recommendations to give me. Should have one sesh'd but I was rained on trying to top out and it became heinous.

ascents.name: Pimpsqueak
ascents.comment: V8/9? Are you sure? How sure? Would you bet on it? One of anything? Cause this went first go after suss. Seems suspect. Anyhow this is rad and an unexpectedly soft quick send that made me really happy that I could still climb "hard" on a shoulder recently dislocated. So pretty up here though. If you can climb V7 definitely try it.

ascents.name: Angry Beaver
ascents.comment: This is an 8? If you say soo... Soft Second GO after the flash attempt. So third go, but whatever.

ascents.name: Fly Boy Sit
ascents.comment: Wow. Such a cool line. Should have M-Flashed, but my fingers numbed out. The first big send of my unsuccessful strike mission to beat Shirley to sending Acid Wash. Anyhow, simulators are sick. Shout out to The Factory 45.

ascents.name: Cocktail sauce
ascents.comment: As far as V8's go, this is pretty soft. Gregor doesn't stand a chance with his fat sausage fingers on that dish. I'd be willing to bet one of anything this never goes for him. Not ever. Even if there's a fire.

ascents.name: Lost, But Not Forgotten
ascents.comment: Had no idea of the misfortunes to come. But this was fun. And I can never remember the name of this one. Also I forget the name. Shoutout Star Wars for being inspirational.

ascents.name: Acid wash right
ascents.comment: The beginning of an epic day at happy valley. Really psyched on finishing this. If you take this at V9 you should get on Fart Fig V6. Same style.

ascents.name: Croft Problem
ascents.comment: Climbs really well, too bad that it drops off.

ascents.name: Morning Dove White
ascents.comment: What a quality V7. Benchmark for the grade. First not soft bolder I've done in a while.

ascents.name: Pow Pow
ascents.comment: Turns out all it took to make this soft was to try it after working beefcake for a couple hours.

ascents.name: Bangalore Torpedo
ascents.comment: Was told this was an 8... no way.

ascents.name: The fuzz
ascents.comment: I love when you find beta that just works perfectly for yourself. This was such a fun time figuring out my beta and then sending with it the first go after finding it. Also, it is a sit start people... Just fyi.

ascents.name: Airtight Garage
ascents.comment: Hey! Want to do a 2 move climb where both are low percentage? Try this!!! 1 star, happy to not have to try this a second sesh.

ascents.name: Tim's Sloper Problem (low)
ascents.comment: -1 stars. Somehow makes Tim's Sloper Problem not fun.

ascents.name: Mindbender
ascents.comment: Couldn't do Golden Boy with the left or right finish so I did this. Its was... okay.

ascents.name: Breakfast at Tiffany's
ascents.comment: Well that's one of the sketchier sends I've had. For a 10ft boulder the fall potential sure is terrifying... I think I'll remember the feeling...

ascents.name: Pavelini
ascents.comment: Finally a morning send to set me on the right track for the day. After days of crazy humid AM conditions, finally had a nice morning. And by morning I mean I probably started at noon. Traveling solo is nice for hitting lots of areas, but Squamish is pretty empty of climbers til 3pm+ so the downside of solo is double big pad trundling up a hill to a new proj and realizing that you need a spot or extra pads... It's been frustrating at times, but luckily I'm getting the hang of this Squamish rock.

ascents.name: Close shave
ascents.comment: What a sweet night send to end the day. Not particularly my style, but styled it out none-the-less. Pretty sweet layback lock off moves lead to a laid back top out and holds filled with pine needles, but needless to say I sent.

ascents.name: Over The Boardwalk
ascents.comment: Can't wait to get back on Left hand...  This was just such a tease.

ascents.name: Blue Flame
ascents.comment: A nice M Flash of a long standing proj. Glad it went quick, "Its Shaaarp!"

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Left of Croft. Pretty fun and beta intensive moves.

ascents.name: High Plains Drifter
ascents.comment: After the Millennium Falcon Van decided to to breath better by bouncing her windshield off on Buttermilk road, you could say I was pretty motivated to makes the most of that drive. And I did. This was the only climb I was really interested in doing this day. Probably the best victory lap top out I've climbed.

ascents.name: Pit Boss
ascents.comment: Another climb I had to watch Maddy do first before realizing how soft and easy it actually was. Only took two sessions 3 years apart.

ascents.name: Left Left Gold Crack Sit
ascents.comment: Almost pulled an LIB style crux when I threw out left, missed, held on, and then threw again. If only I was an LIB I would have sent that go. But I still got it after watching Maddy send. After her accent its probably a V6 now.

ascents.name: Swing Dance
ascents.comment: I guess if you do the bathang maybe it feels like a fun climb. But I didn't because the campus is way softer. And I never want to come back... well maybe for the soft dyno.

ascents.name: Tramslot Traverse
ascents.comment: One fun deadpoint into an okay moving lowball traverse. At least its soft.

ascents.name: Mr. Moran
ascents.comment: After watching a Scott type beta on this mound I propmtly ignored all of it and pumped out on this my first session, only to return the next day to M Flash. The cool part is that Shirley's itch didn't send this so I must be stronger than him again. Because if I do something he doesn't, I'm stronger. I guess I'll take another break from climbing until he can catch up.

ascents.name: Freedom Fighter sit
ascents.comment: Soft sit moves into Soft climb. The perfect problem.

ascents.name: Planet of the Apes
ascents.comment: Unreal how sick this thing is.

ascents.name: Jug Start to Acid Wash Right
ascents.comment: Finally it goes down in an epic night sesh with Kev and Drew Gummy Bear.

ascents.name: The Clapper
ascents.comment: Much better with beta. A lot of non holds are all chalked up from gym gumbies.

ascents.name: Milk the Milks
ascents.comment: What a strange problem. Turns out sending this involves booting up, not being able to pull a single move, raging about it, packing up and putting on your vans, then campusing all but the last 2 moves, rebooting up, and then putting it down. Tis a silly problem, but still easier than King Tut.

ascents.name: Gleaner
ascents.comment: Just glad I didn't blow up my knee

ascents.name: Control Technique
ascents.comment: When boredom strikes...

ascents.name: Iron Man Campus
ascents.comment: Harder than Robinson's Rubber Tester.

ascents.name: The Tugger
ascents.comment: Harnesses my inner Scott and kneebar'd it out. Twas a pretty sweet climb that was my first send in Squamish this trip. Glad it's a top 100 because I really enjoyed the flow. Also tugged one out just behind the boulder so watch your step.

ascents.name: Power Windows
ascents.comment: Not a bad problem. But not the best. Worth doing when your buddies are working on Paul's Cock. Or rock. Whatever.

ascents.name: Malcomb
ascents.comment: Zero stars in the book? Yeah I can see it. Wish I could have done Angus but there was too much snow to do the first move without dragging my girth through it. And by girth I mean butt.

ascents.name: Seven Spanish Angels
ascents.comment: Never would I have expected this to go with my first attempt using the crimp out left.

ascents.name: Ament Arete Sit
ascents.comment: A fun line that doesn't require a crashpad if you can climb it without falling. I fell though. #sorebum

ascents.name: Trailside Arete
ascents.comment: Wow. What a quest to send this. Somehow I totally forgot how to climb for my last trip to Black before the road collapse. So many burns, such little sending. Until it went. Shoutout Shirley for bagging Twilight faster than I got this.

ascents.name: Atlantis
ascents.comment: The reason anyone would do this, if they could, which they should, would be because they could, but they haven't. Shout out to Vin for some should have been obvious (to me) top out beta. This is such a damn fun problem I'll probably run up it every opportunity I get.

ascents.name: Solar power
ascents.comment: Glad to have Shirley spotting. Lots of dramatic catches, I mean spots, left my bottom unscathed and me swooning. Sweep me off my feet Shirley!

ascents.name: Memento Vitae
ascents.comment: I gave this 3 stars because its the hardest I've tried climbing in a long time and I scared my spotters topping out on some of the sturdiest flakes. (out not down) Would I recommend it? Certainly not on 8a, that shit's coveted.

ascents.name: Moondrops
ascents.comment: Well after 2 years of not climbing, I feel confident enough to claim this "The Factory red tag" line. Also the fact that Chris Hoss took 7A+ for this is hilarious. That guy must be super weak.

ascents.name: Ian's Prow
ascents.comment: This was awesome. Definitely my jam, bread, butter, jelly, sexual preference, and style.

ascents.name: G23
ascents.comment: Cool movement up the arete. I was a huge baby trying this thing.

ascents.name: Silent Spotter
ascents.comment: This line is sweet as cake.  The icing is knowing I'm now 53 points further ahead of Shirley Girth.

ascents.name: Only the good die young
ascents.comment: Wow this is ill. Betas are key, but the 3 person send/flash train was awesome. Who needs pads on this thing?

ascents.name: Medusa
ascents.comment: Shirley was angry at this thing. IDK why though, it was casual. Could be 3 stars but some less than ergonomic holds forces me to give 2 stars.

ascents.name: Red Spark
ascents.comment: Fun 2 mover.

ascents.name: The Hulk
ascents.comment: Really cool problem, tricky cross followed by a burly swing was great, but the intro and top out are pretty meh.

ascents.name: Mr. Witty
ascents.comment: One of the best in the happys. Why did I think this was dumb at first??

ascents.name: Wills of Fire
ascents.comment: Holy shit, excellent.

ascents.name: Chips
ascents.comment: Super fun. Cool cross and pogo.

ascents.name: Munchkin Lunge
ascents.comment: mmmm....soft

ascents.name: The Mechanic
ascents.comment: Fun compression, shitty dab boulder.

ascents.name: Bowling Pin Sit
ascents.comment: Sweet climb. Subtle beta makes this much easier and super snack.

ascents.name: Tied to the Whipping Post
ascents.comment: Cool movement on this traverse.

ascents.name: Monkey Bar Right
ascents.comment: Really fun. Coolest on the boulder.

ascents.name: Cave Route
ascents.comment: Soft V6 if you like thuggy climbs.  I enjoyed it.

ascents.name: Sunshine and Lollipops
ascents.comment: Super snack. Bringing some chalk helped on the top.

ascents.name: Molly
ascents.comment: What a lovely boulder to end 2019 on. This was one of the first climbs I tried in Bishop way back with a Jenny Knall type and Fanny Dong giving betas. Good times. Probably my first time back in the sads since 2015. Not so sad anymore.

ascents.name: Strength in Numbers
ascents.comment: Ooooh weee, that was spice-yyy. Shout out to Shirley for the spot because I thought I was going to backflip off the last holds. Turns out, they weren't that last holds and I just don't know how to rock climb.

ascents.name: Mr. Happy
ascents.comment: Fun top out, just here for the days climbed stats.

ascents.name: Viper
ascents.comment: Ah the campus beta. Definitely cooler looking than climbing, but pretty interesting first move!

ascents.name: Swank Stretch
ascents.comment: Wow I did not enjoy this as much as I thought I would. Luckily I finished on it. I mean I finished it. I mean I used my hands inside of its cracks to climb it. Okay I'm done this is dumb.

ascents.name: Prime Time Sit
ascents.comment: Why would you do prime time and not start seated?

ascents.name: Tim's sloper problem
ascents.comment: Another classic completed. Took sending this to get my psych back after flailing on "It's About Time" for like an hour. Luckily this is a much better climb.

ascents.name: Footless traverse
ascents.comment: So pure. (for a traverse) but actually fun movement. Any obviously I'm going to get on a problem with campusing even on a rest day.

ascents.name: The Cube
ascents.comment: So I'm not sure where the real topout is. I see there is a V9?? Crazy. So I did it twice; once mantling from the first 2 slopers on the bottom left and once all the way to the flat cutout up and left. The latter felt V5, but damn was the mantle hard at the bottom...

ascents.name: Go Granny Go
ascents.comment: Climbed the right finish 4 years ago(almost to the day) and couldn't do this. And this trip I warmed up on this lowball dropoff.

ascents.name: The Groveler
ascents.comment: The only groveler I like is my surfboard. This is shit.

ascents.name: Memory Loss
ascents.comment: After watching four “sends” on YouTube I can safely say, everyone else is doing this wrong. IDK how, but no one touched the deadpoint crimp out left that Shirley and I hit before topping out directly above the starting jug. Don't even look twice at those super low right crimpy-doos. But the betas I saw?? Must have been S1 climbers if they thought that line was a V6. (better than the traverse)

ascents.name: Hyperglide
ascents.comment: This was made fun because of the many dogs running below me on the pads while their shitty owners laughed as I was moving through the crux. Its not funny, and you're asshats. The start to a great trip!

ascents.name: Freedom fighter
ascents.comment: Thankfully Scott didn't get permanently lost on the way here because his beta was way softer and more fun.

ascents.name: Hydroponics
ascents.comment: Not a bad line, fun problem solving aspect is really its only redeeming quality though.

ascents.name: Hammerhead
ascents.comment: Holy isht.  I've never committed to anyone as much as I committed to this squanchy line.  So ill.  The drop off is the mental crux.

ascents.name: Pancake House
ascents.comment: Ehh decent movement, crappy top.  Peer pressure from Girley Shirth led to a poor onsight attempt.

ascents.name: The Swedge
ascents.comment: This upside-down pizza slice of a climb is going to make you hungry. Hungry to send that is. Whether your crime is rape, murder, arson, rape, or stampeding cattle through the Vatican , everyone deserves to do some time on this climb.

ascents.name: Green Hornet
ascents.comment: Cool line, fun deadpoint.

ascents.name: Don's Dyno
ascents.comment: Burly.

ascents.name: Done with the South
ascents.comment: Questionable top out moves, but a fun and cool looking problem!

ascents.name: Kill by numbers
ascents.comment: Cool route with fin movement.

ascents.name: Kelly's Arete
ascents.comment: Spicy top out. The beginnings of an excellent Joes trip.

ascents.name: Cobra Kahn
ascents.comment: From the low start. What an awesome feature.

ascents.name: Dyno Time
ascents.comment: Almost didn't flash. Kinda fun.

ascents.name: Sucker Punch
ascents.comment: Cool movement. Fun, but not super rewarding.

ascents.name: Serengeti
ascents.comment: Is this the Kraken?

ascents.name: Groundwater
ascents.comment: Damn this was fun. Lowball, but what a fun swing. For full value forgo the heel hook.

ascents.name: Perfectly Chicken
ascents.comment: I hear you don't even need to top this out for points... but I did anyways.

ascents.name: Flyboy Atrete
ascents.comment: Cool intro into an awkward gaston, but fun.

ascents.name: Anti-Hero
ascents.comment: Epic-ed.

ascents.name: Go Granny Go; Right Finish
ascents.comment: Cool movement.

ascents.name: Beareagle
ascents.comment: mmmm soft....

ascents.name: Son Of Claudius Rufus
ascents.comment: Soft but unique.

ascents.name: Shizam
ascents.comment: First V5!

ascents.name: Shizaam
ascents.comment: First 5! Victory double nut!

ascents.name: Beached Whale
ascents.comment: I give it a V4/5 grade if you top out at the corner overhang instead of campusing around and beached whaling up.  The line goes way cleaner, but probably slightly easier.

ascents.name: Gatorade
ascents.comment: My anti style. Fun problem nonetheless

ascents.name: The Real Thing
ascents.comment: Pretty real.

ascents.name: Fridge center
ascents.comment: Had to get up something today!

ascents.name: Sloppy Poppy
ascents.comment: The 5 year proj goes! Finally in Squamish without a hurt left hammy. Turns out the land of lip traverses is much easier when you can use both heels.

ascents.name: The Huck
ascents.comment: Dunno if I had done this, but I hadn't logged it so here it is. What a fun soft deadpoint.

ascents.name: The Little V4
ascents.comment: Wow look at Natasha's highball. What a beautiful climb. Its proud, it has excellent movement, and best of all, it's right here! Wow You should really try that because it's this problem is lame.

ascents.name: Bear Hug Mantle
ascents.comment: Woah. Didn't expect such a small package to contain so much fun. I understand Fappy's love of little girls now.

ascents.name: Slopers and Dopers
ascents.comment: Meh. Took me a while.

ascents.name: Solar Flare
ascents.comment: This was aesthetic and fun! Wish I had gotten Solar Power as well, but that wasn't working.  I'm just glad I made the topout look better than Director Scott.

ascents.name: Aquaman
ascents.comment: Climbs pretty well, but looks like a turd. Kinda cool pocket/huecos that are unseen from the ground are cool.

ascents.name: Ceramic Salamander
ascents.comment: A straightforward DP on jugs that nearly ripped my hammy. One day I'll have healthy hamstrings...but probably not this summer.

ascents.name: March Arete
ascents.comment: Big Ole DP fun. Wish I had seen slimb's beta before going

ascents.name: Bicycles and Tricycles
ascents.comment: This is spicy. Not Thai Chili spicy, but still frightening. Shoulda onsighted, but Hirley got on first.

ascents.name: Paul Rocks
ascents.comment: 1.5 stars. Screw rounding up. If you're too lazy to put on your climbing shoes but still want to get up a moderate, this is for you.

ascents.name: Act Of Contrivance
ascents.comment: Contrived. Girth holds back. Shirley he should be able to do this...

ascents.name: Beer Tumor right
ascents.comment: Well this wasn't pretty but I'm sure it could be cool with beta!

ascents.name: The Pride
ascents.comment: Holy isht, this was proud. One of my favorite V4's I've done. Bandsox team send.

ascents.name: Stumble bum traverse
ascents.comment: Casual lip traverse

ascents.name: Self service
ascents.comment: Fun movement

ascents.name: Sun in My Eye
ascents.comment: Pretty lame.

ascents.name: Tendons Give
ascents.comment: Cool powerful line.

ascents.name: Zorro
ascents.comment: Fun and cool looking boulder

ascents.name: Ahwahnee Arete
ascents.comment: Scared my spotters cutting feet on the easy top slab. Really cool problem.

ascents.name: Go Go Gorilla
ascents.comment: Fun first move.

ascents.name: Bleached Bones
ascents.comment: meh

ascents.name: Iron Man Traverse
ascents.comment: If Jason Mamoa can do this, I can do this without feet. (used 1 foot or I'd be logging Iron Monkey or whatever its called. Also guesstimating when I did this. (backlog)

ascents.name: Trad Killer
ascents.comment: Fun Line, had to use interesting beta to avoid heel hook on my hurt left hamstring.

ascents.name: Easy in an Easy Chair
ascents.comment: Had to campus the majority due to hurt hamstring. Still fun.

ascents.name: Unknown
ascents.comment: Cool heel hook problem to the right of Reed's Arete.

ascents.name: Tri-Nitro-Toulumne
ascents.comment: Cool climb, but not a 6C

ascents.name: The Angler
ascents.comment: Cool climb. Stiff for the grade, but fun movement.

ascents.name: White Flight
ascents.comment: This is pure. This is highhhhh flyinggg. Super clean line with excellent flow.

ascents.name: Fart Fig
ascents.comment: Probably the sickest, purest, most amazing line in the world. What a turd.

ascents.name: Birthday Direct
ascents.comment: Classic.

ascents.name: Natasha's Highball
ascents.comment: Simply my favorite boulder to date. I recommend drinking half a bottle of Fireball while flailing on Red Dragon before sending.

ascents.name: Shades of the Oldschool
ascents.comment: Added for the stretch factor.  I don't think I'll ever see such a reachy peach ever again.  And I'm not talking about Shirley's shartpile at the Sandbox.

ascents.name: Robinson's Rubber Tester
ascents.comment: Thought this was going to take all season... now for buttermilk stem...

ascents.name: Emerald City
ascents.comment: Best of its grade. You can climb your Summer Vacation all year long and it still wont be as sick.  A climb so nice I did it twice.

ascents.name: Superfly Slab
ascents.comment: Proudest send of my life. I hate slab. I'm pretty sure no one has spent more time on a single send go, ever, on anything.
